## VOICE & TONE RECOMMENDATION

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Recommended Voice | Confident nail editor with a point of view — not a trend reporter, not a tutorial instructor |
| Tone Characteristics | Authoritative but not stiff / Visually led, descriptive / Warm but not overly casual / Directional — gives the reader permission and conviction / Never talks down to the reader |
| Language Style | British English throughout (Mirellè editorial standard). Use "you" directly and often. Lean into sensory descriptors: "sheer burgundy stain", "velvet charcoal", "whispered elegance." Avoid generic phrases like "perfect for any occasion." Never hedge — say "almond is the shape for this aesthetic" not "almond might work well." |
| Audience Match | This reader wants to feel like she's getting advice from someone who *knows* — not a listicle compiler. The confident editorial voice validates her aesthetic choice and gives her the vocabulary to pursue it. |
| Editorial Constraints | British English. No em dashes. No banned vocabulary (do not use: genuinely, honestly, straightforward). No FAQ section. Dense rhythm — short declarative sentences alongside longer descriptive ones. |

